==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''free running''' (''[[uncountable]]'')

#The activity of combining [[Parkour]] with [[gymnastics]] to pass obstacles and demonstrate athletic talent, using impressive gymnastic movements such as somersaults. Most often used in urban environments.

====Synonyms====

===Etymology===
A term introduced by [[Parkour]] practitioner Sebastien Foucan in a programme called Jump London as a synonym for [[Parkour]], the usage has since changed through the adverse reaction of Parkour practitioners to somersaults and non-efficient movements being introduced to the discipline.

